        <abstract>
            <p>The use of earthquakes as a geological cause in his previous letter was careless.</p>
            <p>Shelly beach deposits over considerable distance from Ireland to Scotland seem better explained by high sea-level than low land.</p>
            <p>Only CD seems to have reported shattered rocks under the Moel Tryfan drift.</p>
        </abstract>
